{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b4fd11ce-74bf-4085-923d-dcd81e2f77c7",
    "name": "metacritic_game_api",
    "description": "## Metacritic Game API\n\nThis collection contains GraphQL requests for testing and interacting with the **Metacritic Game API** — a backend service for managing a catalog of video games, including their metadata, genres, platforms, and Metascores.\n\nAll requests are sent as `POST` to the `{{BASE_URL}}` GraphQL endpoint and are organized into three folders:\n\n### Queries\n\nRead-only operations for fetching data from the API:\n\n- Retrieve a list of games with support for **pagination** (limit, offset), **filtering** (by title, minimum Metascore), and **sorting**\n    \n- Fetch a single game by ID, including error handling for invalid IDs\n    \n- List available **genres** and **platforms**\n    \n\n### Mutations\n\nWrite operations for modifying game data:\n\n- **Create**, **update**, and **delete** games\n    \n- Validation scenarios such as creating a game without a required title, using an invalid ID, or performing mutations without an authorization token\n    \n- User registration, including a duplicate email error case\n    \n\n### Auth\n\nAuthentication-related requests:\n\n- Register a new user\n    \n- Log in to obtain an access token\n    \n- Error case for login with an incorrect password\n    \n\n---\n\n**Environment variable used:** `{{BASE_URL}}` — set this to your GraphQL server URL before running requests.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "40513152"
  },
  "item": [
