        {
          "name": "get games",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();\r",
                  "pm.environment.set(\"firstGameId\", json.data.games.games[0].id);\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"No errors\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect(json.errors).to.be.undefined;\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Get games should return games array\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.games.games).to.be.an('array');\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Get games should return totalCount number\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.games.totalCount).to.be.a('number');\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Get games should return hasNextPage\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.games.hasNextPage).to.equal(true);\r",
                  "})\r",
                  ""
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n    \"query\": \"{ games { totalCount hasNextPage games { id title } } }\"\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}",
              "host": [
                "{{BASE_URL}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns a paginated list of games from the Metacritic Game API GraphQL endpoint.\n\n- **Method/URL**: `POST {{BASE_URL}}`\n- **Content-Type**: `application/json`\n- **Endpoint style**: GraphQL over HTTP (query in JSON body)\n\n## GraphQL operation\nThis request sends a GraphQL query that selects the `games` connection and its pagination metadata.\n\n### Query shape\n```graphql\n{\n  games {\n    totalCount\n    hasNextPage\n    games {\n      id\n      title\n      # ...additional fields may be selected depending on the query in the body\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Variables / configuration\nThis request relies on the following Postman variable(s):\n\n- `{{BASE_URL}}` *(environment: `metacritic_game_api_env`)* — Base URL for the GraphQL endpoint.\n\n> Note: The current query shown in the request body does not use GraphQL variables (e.g. `$limit`, `$offset`). If you later add variables, you’d send them alongside the query in a `variables` object.\n\n## Example request body\nRaw JSON (GraphQL query as a string):\n```json\n{\n  \"query\": \"{ games { totalCount hasNextPage games { id title } } }\"\n}\n```\n\n## Expected response shape\nA successful response is expected to be JSON with a `data` object and **no** top-level `errors`.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"data\": {\n    \"games\": {\n      \"totalCount\": 123,\n      \"hasNextPage\": true,\n      \"games\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": 1,\n          \"title\": \"Example Title\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Tests\nThe request’s **Tests** script validates:\n\n- **HTTP 200** status code.\n- **No GraphQL errors**: `json.errors` is `undefined`.\n- `json.data.games.games` is an **array**.\n- `json.data.games.totalCount` is a **number**.\n- `json.data.games.hasNextPage` is **true**.\n\nThese checks ensure the endpoint is reachable, the GraphQL operation executed without errors, and the key pagination fields are present with the expected types."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "get games with limit",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();\r",
                  "pm.environment.set(\"firstGameId\", json.data.games.games[0].id);\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"No errors\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect(json.errors).to.be.undefined;\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Get games should have limit of 10\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.games.games).to.have.lengthOf(10)\r",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n    \"query\": \"{ games(limit: 10) { totalCount hasNextPage games { id title } } }\"\r\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}",
              "host": [
                "{{BASE_URL}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "### Purpose\n\nRetrieves a paginated list of games from the Metacritic Game API using a GraphQL query with an explicit `limit`.\n\nThis request is useful for:\n\n- verifying pagination metadata (`totalCount`, `hasNextPage`)\n    \n- fetching a predictable number of game items\n    \n- capturing the first returned game id for use in subsequent requests\n    \n\n---\n\n### Endpoint / Environment\n\n- **URL**: `{{BASE_URL}}`\n    \n- **Method**: `POST`\n    \n- **Header**: `Content-Type: application/json`\n    \n\n#### Required environment variables\n\n- `BASE_URL` (environment: `metacritic_game_api_env`)\n    \n\n---\n\n### GraphQL query shape\n\nThis request sends a GraphQL query in the JSON body (string field `query`).\n\nHigh-level shape:\n\n``` graphql\n{\n  games(limit: 10) {\n    totalCount\n    hasNextPage\n    games {\n      id\n      title\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n ```\n\n---\n\n### Example request body\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"query\": \"{ games(limit: 10) { totalCount hasNextPage games { id title } } }\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n---\n\n### Expected response fields\n\nOn success (no GraphQL errors), the response body is expected to contain:\n\n- `data.games.totalCount` — total number of games available\n    \n- `data.games.hasNextPage` — boolean indicating if more pages exist after this one\n    \n- `data.games.games[]` — array of game objects\n    - `id` — game identifier\n        \n    - `title` — game title\n        \n\n#### Example response snippet\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"data\": {\n    \"games\": {\n      \"totalCount\": 123,\n      \"hasNextPage\": true,\n      \"games\": [\n        { \"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Example Game\" }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n ```\n\n---\n\n### Notes about tests / chaining\n\nThe existing test script:\n\n- validates HTTP **200** and that `errors` is **undefined**\n    \n- asserts the returned array length is **10**\n    \n- sets environment variable `firstGameId` from the first item:\n    - `firstGameId = json.data.games.games[0].id`"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "get games with offset",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();\r",
                  "const firstGameId = pm.environment.get(\"firstGameId\")\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Status 200\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"No errors\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect(json.errors).to.be.undefined;\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Offset should skip first game\", function () {\r",
                  "    const ids = json.data.games.games.map(game => game.id);\r",
                  "    pm.expect(ids).to.not.include(firstGameId)\r",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n    \"query\": \"{ games(limit: 10, offset: 1) { totalCount hasNextPage games { id title } } }\"\r\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}",
              "host": [
                "{{BASE_URL}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "## Overview\n\nThis request retrieves a paginated list of games from the GraphQL API using an **offset**.\n\n- **Method**: `POST`\n    \n- **URL**: `{{BASE_URL}}`\n    \n- **Content-Type**: `application/json`\n    \n\nIt is intended to validate that pagination via `offset` correctly **skips** the first item returned by a previous call (whose id is stored in `firstGameId`).\n\n## Required variables\n\nThis request depends on these environment variables (active env: `metacritic_game_api_env`):\n\n- `BASE_URL` — Base URL for the GraphQL endpoint.\n    \n- `firstGameId` — The id of the first game returned by a prior request (used to verify the offset behavior).\n    \n\n## Request payload (GraphQL)\n\nThe request sends a JSON body with a GraphQL query in the `query` field.\n\nExample payload:\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"query\": \"{ games(limit: 10, offset: 1) { totalCount hasNextPage games { id title } } }\"\n}\n\n ```\n\nNotes:\n\n- `limit: 10` requests up to 10 games.\n    \n- `offset: 1` skips the first game in the full result set.\n    \n\n## Expected response shape\n\nA successful response is expected to be JSON with the following shape:\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"data\": {\n    \"games\": {\n      \"totalCount\": 123,\n      \"hasNextPage\": true,\n      \"games\": [\n        { \"id\": 1, \"title\": \"...\" }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n ```\n\nWhere:\n\n- `data.games.totalCount` is the total number of games available.\n    \n- `data.games.hasNextPage` indicates whether more results are available beyond the current window.\n    \n- `data.games.games[]` is the page of game objects, each including at minimum `id` and `title`.\n    \n\n## Included tests\n\nThe post-response tests validate:\n\n1. **Status 200** — the request succeeds (`HTTP 200`).\n    \n2. **No GraphQL errors** — `errors` is not present in the response.\n    \n3. **Offset behavior** — the returned list of ids does **not** include `{{firstGameId}}`, confirming that `offset: 1` skipped the first result."
          },
          "response": []
        },
